The '''[https://brooklynwaldorf.org Brooklyn Waldorf School]''' is a coeducational, independent, non-sectarian day preschool and elementary [[Waldorf education|Waldorf school]] located in [[Bedford–Stuyvesant, Brooklyn|Bedford-Stuyvesant, Brooklyn,]] [[New York City|New York]]. The School operates on the principles of [[Waldorf education|Waldorf Education]], and adapts the traditional methods of Rudolf Steiner to the unique, urban environment of Brooklyn, New York. The school's mission is to provide Waldorf education to the economically, culturally and racially diverse community of Brooklyn. The school was founded in 2005 and currently has a Preschool/Kindergarten and Grades 1-8. In 2011, the Brooklyn Waldorf School moved into its new home at the [https://brooklynwaldorf.org/about/ Claver Castle]. The School uses a tiered financial aid [[Tuition payments|tuition]] model to help achieve diversity of students.

The Brooklyn Waldorf School is a “developing status” member of the [http://awsna.org/ Association of Waldorf Schools of North America] (AWSNA).<ref name=awsna>[http://www.members.awsna.org/Public/SchoolListPage.aspx AWSNA Member School List]. Accessed 2008-10-16.</ref>

